i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Margaret De Poynings was born about 1126, in Poynings, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. She married Adam de Poynings II about 1150, in Crawley, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons."},"et":{"ABT 1126–":"umbes 1126–Surnud","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1112–Male":"1112–Surnud","1128–1147":"1128–1147","1160–1243":"1160–1243","1173–Male":"1173–Surnud","1126–Female":"1126–Surnud","ABT 1150":"umbes 1150","1128":"1128","1126":"1126","1147":"1147","1202":"1202","1112":"1112","about 1128":"umbes 1128","1243":"1243","       1173":"1173","ABT 1126":"umbes 1126","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","Crawley, Sussex, England":"Crawley, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Poynings, Sussex, England":"Poynings, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Poynings,Sussex,England":"Poynings, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1126–":"noin 1126–Kuollut","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1112–Male":"1112–Kuollut","1128–1147":"1128